com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?w=822&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 822w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=210%2C123&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 210w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=768%2C448&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="74576" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/flowingdata-at-17/keep-on-going/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=822%2C480&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="822,480" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="keep-on-going" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=822%2C480&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" tabindex="0" role="button" /></a></p><p>上周标志着互联网这个小角落在数据可视化方面的运行 17 周年。感谢<a href="https://flowingdata.com/membership/">FlowingData 过去和现在的成员</a>。谢谢阅读。没有你们，这个网站就不存在。</p><p>感觉并没有那么久，但也很难记得我没有在 FlowingData 上工作的时候。</p><p>在撰写<a href="https://book.flowingdata.com/">《Visualize This》</a>第二版时，我想起了这些年来可视化的变化。不同的工具、不同的设备和不同的数据集。经过多年制作图表后，我对数据和可视化的看法有所不同。</p><p>可视化的范围不同。它已经变得更好，超越了快速分析。</p><p>互联网则不同。为了结束 FlowingData 两周年纪念日，我感谢读者通过 Twitter、Digg 和 del.icio.us 向我发送链接，这些链接如今已与最初的形式相去甚远。</p><p>尽管如此，在这个网站上工作对我来说还是很有趣的。我仍然喜欢探索数据。也许比我刚开始的时候更重要。我仍然对人们如何创造性地处理数据感到兴奋。我仍然感谢互联网之神让我做到了这一点。</p><p>再次感谢。</p><p>到明年。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/birthday/" rel="tag">生日</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 74552</post-id></item><item><title>缩小到原子大小</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/shrinking-down-to-the-size-of-an-atom/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Tue, 02 Jul 2024 07:32:37 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Infographics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Epic Spaceman]]></category><category><![CDATA[scale]]></category><category><![CDATA[small]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=74527 </guid><description><![CDATA[In a different take on showing the scale of very tiny things, Epic&#8230;<p><strong>标签:</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/epic-spaceman/" rel="tag">史诗太空人</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/scale/" rel="tag">规模</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/small/" rel="tag">小</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="iframe-container"><iframe class="youtube-player" width="1090" height="614" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rn9dkV4sVYQ?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent" allowfullscreen="true" style="border:0;" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox"></iframe></p><p> 《Epic Spaceman》以不同的方式展示了非常微小的物体的尺寸，它从人类大小开始，每 21 秒缩小十次。</p><p><strong>标签:</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/epic-spaceman/" rel="tag">史诗太空人</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/scale/" rel="tag">规模</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/small/" rel="tag">小</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 74527</post-id></item><item><title>世界领导人和他们所服务的人群之间的年龄差异</titl